<br>
Mages have always been responsible for the burst-damage in a group with the pet offering sustained DPS. My theory is to have the fire pets being sustained DPS via non-melee wth the Magician STILL being burst non-melee DPS. <br>
<br>
Firstly, all pets are not constrained by manna. One spell from the list is randomly selected, cast then upon completion another is selected. (since NPCs do not have re-cast delays) This keeps the pet as good as perma rooted because it should always be casting a spell or following its master. <br>
<br>
Measuring the DPS of other pets through melee, it seems logical to apply the same DPS levels to the magic-based damage. 61+ pets tend to peak at around 100 DPS <br>
<br>
<br>
Vocarate: Fire (Level 44-45) <br>
<br>
Self buff: <br>
Arch Shielding <br>
Diamond Skin <br>
Elemental Armour <br>
O'Keil's Flickering Flame <br>
FireElementalAura <br>
<br>
Chain-casts: <br>
Flame Shock (110DD) - 44DPS <br>
Garrison's Mighty Manna Shock (148DD) - 53DPS <br>
Frost Shock (187DD) - 60DPS <br>
Tishan's Clash (50DD + Stun) <br>
<br>
These spells are aproximately 44-60DPS. Factoring in partial resists due to the Level disparity, and the peak DPS is roughly 50. <br>
<br>
<br>
Greater Vocaration: Fire (Level 48-49) <br>
<br>
Self buff: <br>
Arch Shielding <br>
Diamond Skin <br>
Elemental Armour <br>
O'Keil's Flickering Flame <br>
FireElementalAura <br>
<br>
Chain-casts: <br>
Inferno Shock (250DD) - 69DPS <br>
Ice Shock (320DD) - 76DPS <br>
Lightning Shock (405DD) - 84DPS <br>
Tishan's Clash (50DD + Stun) <br>
<br>
<br>
Child of Ro (Level 60-61) <br>
<br>
Self buff: <br>
Shield of the Magi <br>
Manaskin <br>
Elemental Cloak <br>
O'Keil's Flickering Flame <br>
FireElementalAura <br>
<br>
Chain-casts: <br>
Ice Shock (320DD) - 76DPS <br>
Lightning Shock (405DD) - 84DPS <br>
Conflagaration (606DD) - 110DPS <br>
Tishan's Clash (50DD + Stun) <br>
<br>
Due to the massive level disparity beween GV:F and CoR, perhapse Conflagaration should be dropped from the list and Inferno Shock put back in, basically the same lineup as GV:F but with increased accuracy due to being 12 levels higher. But the lower damage output of Ice Shock and Lightning Shock could compensate for the massive power of Conflagaration.<br>
<br>
The downsides to this being that each spell is cast randomly, my theory being that pets should not chain-cast the same spell, but one of those available to them, then a chance at a different one afterwards. On mobs immune to certain effects, this can be counter-productive since hitting a Fire Giant with Inferno Shock will not damage it.<br>
<br>
Crunching the numbers, the fire elemental currently has a MASSIVE potential as a burst-damage pet, but this is now what pets are.<br>
<br>
Would this proposed fix be acceptable by your (as the wizard community) standards? Thanks for constructive criticisms and comments. <p>Majishia Vie &lt;Wyrd Angles&gt;<br>
Conjurer of the 56th Bummed Summoning<br>
Antonius Bayle<br>
